Description: Scarab in glazed composition, probably mould-made; underside decorated with unclear motif, possibly debased hieroglyphs.
Curator's comments: Scarab not yet located, published by Gardner (in Gardner 1888, pl. XVIII, no. 37). Gardner, E. A. 1888, Naukratis. Part II (Sixth Memoir of the Egypt Exploration Fund), London.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (OC.132) (phase 3)
